        Cheat Sheet -Java

Data Types

- int
- float
- double
- String 
- long
- boolean

Conditional

- ==
- <=
- >=
- <
- >

If-Else

- if(condition){
	-----
} 
else{
	-----
}

- if(condition){
	
}
else if(condition){
	--
}

else{
	---
}

- condition?true:false


loops

- for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
	System.out.println(i);
}

- while(condition){
	----
}

- Enhanced for--- for(int i : list){
	print(---)
}

Switch

switch(some variable){
	case 0:
	do something
	break;
}


Strings

- length()--length if String
- split("")--break a string based on some regex
- concat -- concat two Strings
- trim() -- removing spaces

Math

- abs() - calculate absolute valyue
- max() - calculate max value
- min() - calculate min value
- floor() - round up to down
- ceil() - round up to up

Array

- initialisation 
int[] a = new int[size]
length() - size of array

-multidimensional(Array of arrays) - int[][] = new int[size][size]

ArrayList

-size()-size of list
-add() - add element at last
-remove()- remove mentioned element from list

Conversion

Integer.parseInt(val)--converts to int
String.valueOf(val) - converts to String
Double.parseDouble() - converts to double
.intValue()
.toString()




